28/07/2003
MITROVICA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kosovo Parliament member Oliver Ivanovic told reporters Sunday (27 July) that the province should organise a referendum on Serbia's new constitution. He said Serbs in the province should have the right to weigh in on the constitution, and asked the international community to support requests for a referendum to that effect. Ivanovic is a member of the Kosovo Serb coalition Povratak. (Tanjug, BBC - 27/07/03)
